description: The ground-breaking and controversial Lost Girls will now be available in a super-deluxe, yet affordable, single-volume hardcover edition! For more than a century, Alice, Wendy, and Dorothy have been our guides through the Wonderland, Neverland, and the Land of Oz of our childhoods. Now like us, these three lost girls have grown up and are ready to guide us again, this time through the realms of our sexual awakening and fulfillment. Through their familiar fairy tales they share with us their most intimate revelations of desire in its many forms, revelations that shine out radiantly through the dark clouds of war gathering around a luxury Austrian hotel. Drawing on the rich heritage of erotica, Lost Girls is the rediscovery of the power of ecstatic writing and art in a sublime union that only the medium of comics can achieve. Exquisite, thoughtful, and human, Lost Girls is a work of breathtaking scope that challenges the very notion of art fettered by convention. This is erotic fiction at its finest.
name: HC

description: ComicsLit presents Nabiel Kanan's graphic novel about a young girl on vacation with her family, who meets another somewhat older girl, who is there on her own. Free-spirited, mysterious, even possibly dangerous, her new acquaintance is fascinating, and her rebellious ways alluring, yet she remains frustratingly elusive.
name: GN

description: How does an up-start vigilante make a name for himself? By declaring war on the Cross...the largest crime syndicate in the United States. Unfortunately for the Revisionist, the leader of the Cross has been alive since the dawn of man and is more than ready for the challenge!
name: GN

description: Andi Watson's latest series reaches its penultimate chapter. With the church booked and the wedding back on, everything should be rosey for Louise and Rob. However, the forthcoming marital bliss is soured by Rob not finding work and digging deeper into a rut of apathy and daytime TV. Meanwhile, Lou, having finished her college course, can't find employment without work experience. Her patience and sympathy for Rob ebbs further away as she finds she's left with only one course of action left.

description: War is Hell, but what lies beneath the blood-soaked battlefield of an isolated French village caught between two opposing forces is much worse than either side has ever imaged. Confusion sets in amidst the carnage and both sides are forced into a reluctant partnership to survive the night.

description: Far away, in a world much like our own, there lived the Desperadoes, the greatest heroes the universe has ever known. They fought in many wars and after a lifetime of struggle, won peace. But even as the Desperadoes retired to raise families, they realized that more challenges lay ahead. The United Empires Government, set up after the fall of the last of the great tyrants, has slowly deteriorated over the years. New and more powerful enemies lie in wait, ones who may have allowed the all the former tyrants to fail in order to fulfill a grand mysterious scheme. And in the midst of all this, the heroes face their greatest challenge: to raise children - some of them eager to pursue the way, others reluctant to follow in their fathers’ footsteps. This is the story of one extraordinary family’s struggle to live life in an ever-changing world in an ever-changing universe. In this prequel story to his Battle Girlz series, creator Rod Espinosa once again shows his ability to create entire new universes and populate them with beings who mix the extraordinary with the familiar, presenting the reader with delightful flights of fantasy that still let you know they're grounded in reality.

Halloween has descended and Lavender is boarding up her magic store before the tsunami of costumed toddlings emerge from the night to gorge themselves on the surrounding residents' sweet individually wrapped offerings. As they force their way through the cracks in her security, Lavender lapses into a flashback of her first traumatic childhood Halloween with her quirky, faster-than-the-speed-of-light assistant, Saiko. Saiko takes the spirit of Halloween way too far when she devises a plan to collect all the candy in the world and store it in Lavender's house. Now Lavender must find a way to stop Saiko's candy crime spree before her house bursts like a piñata and her parents force her to wear the little fairy princess costume she despises so much. A sweet Halloween treat featuring Saiko & Lavender in all of their childhood glory, from the creators behind Monsters of Rock and True Hue!

Premier Double-sized issue. A great moneymaking scheme has come to the land of Darkwood. With the help of a legend-savvy maiden, Mayor Moore has put unicorn steak on the menu and his town on the map. Will his only daughter, Rose, join the family trade or burn her city to the ground trying to stop him? Darkwood—a fairy tale for bastards

The battle for Unicorn Town continues! Rose searches the underworld for assistance in ending Raynd's career, while the Mayor looks into publishing his memoirs. Featuring funny animals, a parade of useless malcontents, a military-grade aphrodisiac, and a violent look at Raynd's adventures in people-hunting. Darkwood, a fairy tale for bastards!

Rose has succeeded: The unicorn hunter Raynd has been defeated, but the forests are more dangerous than ever! While Ira investigates the origin of Moore and his fantastic meat-packing operation, the unicorns plan an attack on their poachers. Watch out, those horns are sharper than you've been led to believe!

The exciting end to the Unicorn Hunters miniseries! Rose and Ira's schemes backfire, leaving a fire-breathing unicorn to immolate and perforate the citizens of Unicorntown. When an evil perversion of nature battles an equally evil plutocrat, the fate of the land lies with a senseless, spoiled brat and an opportunist rare-animal hunter. Marvel in shock and amazement as everything goes wrong!

description: When Dilbert first appeared in newspapers across the country in 1989, office workers looked around suspiciously. Was its creator, Scott Adams, a pen name for someone who worked amongst them? After all, the humor was just too eerily funny and familiar. Since then, Dilbert has become more than a cartoon character. He's become an office icon. In Another Day in Cubicle Paradise Dilbert and his cohorts, Dogbert, Catbert, Ratbert, and the pointy-haired boss, once again entertain with their cubicle humor. From bizarre personnel decisions to meetings gone bad, from schizoid secretaries to consultants from hell, Another Day in Cubicle Paradise provides a way to get all those darn comic strips off the breakroom bulletin board.

description:
In this, the most typical of fantasy worlds, magic mingles with science, and spooky and awesome creatures inhabit the ancient forests. Something, though, is… wrong. In addition to dragons and damsels, Darkwood is filled with a few modern problems: natives slaughtered by overzealous real-estate developers, a fantastic species on the brink of extinction, and a woman who has combined her maidenhood and hunting skill to form an economic juggernaut!

Collects Legends From Darkwood

description:
Shelley is knocking some heads together and seeing what pops out – in this case it’s cogs and sparks, as Dandridge: The Copper Conspiracy hots up with some shiny robot action!

Also in this week’s Prog – Judge Dredd and Judge Hamida begin to narrow their search for the suicide cult preying on Mega-City One’s remaining population, there are bizarre goings-on under the streets of London in Stickleback: Number of the Beat, was bringing Zombo back from the dead a good idea in Planet Zombo, and we begin a new three-part Tharg’s 3rillers with a quest for a mythical ghostship in The Ghostship Mathematica!
